/* September–October */ Common USMC practice for writing Battalion names is with a slash between the battalion number and regiment number, rather than a dash as previously typed. Thus, 1st Battalion, 6th Marines would be represented as 1/6 and "one six" when spoken. (The word "Regiment" is often dropped when Marine Regiments are referenced. Hence, 6th Marine Regiment is commonly referred to as "6th Marines" for example.)
